<TITLE> Accountability can cut graft: PM </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 22 (bdnews24.com) - Prime minister Sheikh Hasina stressed Sunday on accountability in private and public sectors to curb corruption, an aide said. "Accountability has to be ensured at public and private sectors. It will help cut down corruption," she was quoted as telling a delegation of German parliament. The prime minister's press secretary Abul Kalam Azad briefed the media on the meeting. The five-member delegation of the "Parliamentary Friendship Group for Relations with the States of South Asia of the German Bundestag" came here on Feb. 20 on a five-day visit. Sebastian Edathy, chairman of the Group, led the German parliamentarians to the meeting with the Hasina, the leader of the House, at her parliament office in the evening. Norman Paech, Hans-Peter Thul, Holger Ortel and Steffen Reiche are the other members. Azad said Hasina emphasised joint efforts to curb terrorism and militancy. She sought German assistance to generate solar-powered electricity to ease power and energy crisis. Before the meeting, a seven-strong delegation led by Japan's deputy foreign minister Seiko Hashimoto met her for an hour. The Japanese team congratulated Hasina on the landslide victory of her party in the general election, Azad said Hasina called for increased Japanese assistance in communications, health and education. Foreign minister Dipu Moni was present at the meeting. bd
